    "created_at": "2015-01-16T11:37:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-16T11:37:53Z",
    "body": "You don't actually need to build `librustc_driver` twice, you can have two `rustc` binaries built with the same libs, but different configs for `src/driver/driver.rs`.\nI would suggest having the default set a TLS key before calling into `librustc_driver`, while the release version wouldn't do that extra step. The build system could then package `bin/rustc-stable` (or whatever name it would have) as `bin/rustc` for the release.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
